# Quick Dev — communication with Guillaume

During any **quick-dev** session (`bmad-quick-dev`, or an explicit “build / fix / implement this” run that follows that workflow):

## Clarity bar (non-negotiable)

Shared SSOT: `_bmad/custom/clarity-bar-fr.md`.

**Phrase-test before every important message** (including internal review findings and the final presentation): if Guillaume would reply « Reformule en langage naturel, sans jargon excessif », rewrite. He must never need to ask.

The Quick Dev **review phase** has the **same** clarity requirement as `bmad-code-review` (En bref → Verdict → structured findings → Recommandation BMad).

## Language and tone

- Respond **in French** in chat.
- Use **simple, accessible language** — no unnecessary jargon or unexplained technical English.
- Briefly define any unavoidable technical term on first use (e.g. « APVTS = stockage des paramètres du plugin »).
- Write in **complete sentences** — no telegraphic bullet chains or keyword dumps.
- Never respond to Guillaume in English during quick-dev chat, even when subagents, specs, or diffs are in English.
- Technical evidence (paths, AC ids, symbols) only as a short trailing line — not in the main meaning-bearing sentences.

## Artifacts vs chat

- **Chat** with Guillaume → French + clarity bar.
- **Generated artifacts** (spec file, code map, suggested review order in the spec) → English (`document_output_language`), unless Guillaume asks otherwise.

## Structure for important messages

1. **En bref** — one sentence on what you understood / what was done / what will be done.
2. Details in plain French.
3. For **each decision with options**, always add **Recommandation BMad** (mandatory — never skip):
   - **Option recommandée** — number and short label
   - **Pourquoi** — 2–4 accessible sentences
   - **Confiance** — `ferme` or `nuancée` (if several options are defensible, say so and still pick one)

## BMad workflow terms → French (user-facing)

| Internal | Say to Guillaume |
|----------|------------------|
| `draft` | brouillon |
| `ready-for-dev` | prêt à développer |
| `in-progress` | en cours |
| `in-review` | prêt pour revue |
| `oneshot` | passage direct (sans grosse spec) |
| Acceptance criteria / AC | critères d’acceptance |
| Code Map | carte du code |
| Suggested Review Order | ordre de relecture suggéré |
| `decision-needed` / `patch` / `defer` | décision à prendre / correction à appliquer / à reporter |

## Subagents

Subagents may output English or dense technical prose. **Always reformulate** in plain French before presenting to Guillaume — especially review output. Full contract: `_bmad/custom/quick-dev-presentation-fr.md`.
